dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Santner run out (Mohammad Nawaz/†Sarfaraz Ahmed) 1 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: looks like Santner could be run out first ball. Yes he is. Gets a short ball going across him. It's skidding fast as he pulls and he chips it wide of long-on off the high part of the bat. This mistimed shot allows them a thought about the second run - which CDG calls for and is close to completing. Nawaz fires the throw to the striker's end on the bounce. Sarfraz picks up and beats Santner's dive by a long way

dismissalText.commentary: Haris Sohail c Henry b Santner 63 (87b 5x4 0x6 140m) SR: 72.41

dismissalComment.html: that increasing asking rate has resulted in a wicket. Nicely tossed up from Santner, down leg, 77 kph after a 96 kph first delivery. Haris comes down, but is deceived by that lack of pace as he tries to loft the ball straight. Santner's direction of spin means the ball was always going to skew away to long-on if he didn't time it, as is the case here. But a lovely rearguard effort from Haris

dismissalText.commentary: Shadab Khan c Nicholls b Santner 54 (77b 5x4 0x6 93m) SR: 70.12

dismissalComment.html: is that the game? It's another lovely display of defensive, but attacking spin bowling. He knows Shadab is going to come so he tosses it up, but wide outside off. Shadab runs down, looking to hit the ball over cover. Instead, it skews off the outside half to short third man. Just like how de Grandhomme got out to Chahal in the second ODI in Pune last year. It's a defensive attacking option, oxymoron-ish as it may be

dismissalComment.html: edged and taken this time. 142 kph, full delivery outside off. Amin drives with his hands well way from the body, and the ball hardly moves. Finds the outside edge and carries low to Taylor at wide slip, straight inside. Quality catch. Henry's extra pace meant Amin's feet weren't where it should have been

headshotImage.caption: Fakhar Azam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Fakhar Azam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Henry strikes again, and Pakistan's struggles continue. It was full outside off, Zaman clears his front leg, his back foot moves nowhere. All he does is chip a catch to mid-off. That's a terrible stroke, not sure what he was trying to do, go over cover or hit it along the ground.

headshotImage.caption: Babar Azam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Babar Azam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: 140 kph, edged and another one. Henry on a roll. But not much Azam could do about that. Fantastic bowling. Full length outside off, fifth-stump channel, the ball moves away late. Takes the thick outside edge to second slip. No trouble at all. All down to Henry's pace again, Azam a fraction of a second later to the ball

and that's the game. It doesn't go to the last over, but that was a sensational finish to the ODI series. A short slower delivery outside off, Raees swats it away towards midwicket, who keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a reverse-cupped catch. New Zealand complete a 5-0 sweep in the ODIs

commentPostTextItems.html: 6.55pm In the setting sun in Wellington, New Zealand sweep Pakistan with another clinical display. Only this time, they had to contend with a strong Pakistan fight. It was another stuttering innings from Pakistan in the first 25 overs, but they put up arguably their best period of cricket in this series in the latter half of this innings.

Shadab Khan and Haris Sohail struck fine rearguard fifties to put Pakistan in a position from which they could at least fight. They needed 100 off 60, and they took it down to the penultimate over. But fell agonizingly short in a thrilling finish to the ODIs.

Martin Guptill is the Man of the Match and the Man of the Series: "Skidding on with the new ball. Precautionary to get off, the shoulder is fine. Reasonable form, not my most fluent work, but sometimes, you have to score the tough runs. We've had to do a lot of hard grafts with the bat."

Kane Williamson: "They (Pakistan) operated well on that surface. Our guys adapted well right through the series. The surfaces have been slightly on the slower side, credit to Pakistan's side. Singles were hard to come by. ODI cricket is fickle in its nature. It is about improving all the time.
Sarfraz Ahmed: "Very tough series, the main thing was batting, it didn't click right through the series. We had opportunities. We back our team."
